.TH "spi_mem_exec_op" 9 "spi_mem_exec_op" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spi_mem_exec_op \- Execute a memory operation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" spi_mem_exec_op
.BI "(struct spi_mem *mem "  ","
.BI "const struct spi_mem_op *op "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mem" 12
the SPI memory
.IP "op" 12
the memory operation to execute
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Executes a memory operation.

This function first checks that \fIop\fP is supported and then tries to execute
it.
.SH "RETURN"
0 in case of success, a negative error code otherwise.
